{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17409899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17409899"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260885"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260885"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15151"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17534604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17534604"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:48:06+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:48:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15151"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260885","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1260885"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T05:07:19+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T06:22:58+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"new","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":1,"questionsAnswered":0,"marksTotal":0,"marksAttainable":0,"marksAttempted":0,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T05:07:19+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"15151","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15151"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.68,0.13,0.07,0.04,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7839"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60332"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7839","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7839"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15151"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45754"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1889"},{"type":"tags","id":"2173"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2545"},{"type":"tags","id":"3426"},{"type":"tags","id":"9051"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19109"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60332","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/60332"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of fever, night sweats, fatigue, and joint pain. The fever pattern is intermittent, with symptoms improving and worsening every few days. He works as a sheep farmer in rural Australia. He regularly consumes unpasteurised goat\u0027s milk and cheese from his neighbour\u0027s farm. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 95/min, blood pressure 125/75 mmHg, respiratory rate 18/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 38.5\u00b0C. He has tender cervical lymphadenopathy and mild hepatosplenomegaly. His joints appear normal with a full range of movement.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely causative organism?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Brucella species","Bartonella henselae","Legionella pneumophila","Francisella tularensis","Leptospira interrogans"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of brucellosis, including undulating fever, night sweats, arthralgia, and constitutional symptoms. The history of consumption of unpasteurised dairy products and occupational exposure to sheep are significant risk factors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBrucella species\u003C/strong\u003E are the causative organisms of brucellosis. They primarily affect livestock such as sheep, goats, and cattle. Transmission occurs via contact with infected animals or consuming contaminated animal products, particularly unpasteurised dairy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBartonella henselae\u003C/strong\u003E causes cat scratch disease, which typically presents with regional lymphadenopathy following a cat scratch or bite. While it can cause fever and constitutional symptoms, the lack of cat exposure and the undulating fever pattern make this diagnosis less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELegionella pneumophila\u003C/strong\u003E causes Legionnaires\u0027 disease, which typically presents with pneumonia, high fever, and respiratory symptoms. The organism is usually acquired through inhalation of contaminated water droplets from cooling towers or other water systems, which does not fit this clinical scenario.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFrancisella tularensis\u003C/strong\u003E causes tularaemia, which is primarily transmitted through tick bites or contact with infected rabbits and rodents. The presentation typically includes a primary ulcer at the site of inoculation, which is not present in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeptospira interrogans\u003C/strong\u003E causes leptospirosis, which typically presents with more acute onset of symptoms and is associated with exposure to water or soil contaminated with animal urine. The undulating fever pattern is not typical of leptospirosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe diagnosis of brucellosis is confirmed through blood cultures and serological testing. Treatment typically involves a combination of antibiotics such as doxycycline plus rifampicin or gentamicin for 6-8 weeks to prevent relapse.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Brucellosis commonly presents with undulating fever, night sweats, and arthralgia after exposure to unpasteurised dairy products or infected animals.","Brucella species are the causative organisms of brucellosis, transmitted through contact with infected animals or their products.","Occupational exposure (farmers, veterinarians, abattoir workers) is a significant risk factor for brucellosis."],"references":["Qureshi KA, Parvez A, Fahmy NA, et al. Brucellosis: epidemiology, pathogenesis, diagnosis and treatment-a comprehensive review. Ann Med. 2023;55(2):2295398. doi:10.1080/07853890.2023.2295398"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45754"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15151"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/45754"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-10T21:56:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-10T21:57:38+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7839"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60332"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"ty